{"title_page": "Wan Lijun", "text_new": "{{Chinese name|[[Wan (surname)|Wan]]}}\n'''Wan Lijun''' ({{lang-zh|\u4e07\u7acb\u9a8f}}, born July 1957) is a Chinese chemist, specializing in [[electrochemistry]] and [[surface science]]. He is an academician of the [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]] and a former president of the [[University of Science and Technology of China]].\n\n==Career==\nWan graduated from [[Dalian University of Technology]] in 1982 and received his PhD degree at [[Tohoku University]] in 1996.<ref name=\"ICCAS\">{{cite web |title=Prof. Li-Jun Wan |url=http://spm.iccas.ac.cn/wanlijun/People/wljys/ |publisher=ICCAS |accessdate=19 July 2019}}</ref> He has been a professor at Institute of Chemistry, Chinese Academy of Sciences (ICCAS) since 1999, and was the director of ICCAS from 2004 to 2013. Afterwards, he directed the Beijing National Laboratory for Molecular Sciences and the Key Laboratory of Molecular Nanostructure and Nanotechnology, CAS.<ref>{{cite news |title=WAN Lijun Named as the new President of USTC |url=https://en.ustc.edu.cn/highlight/201503/t20150327_213296.html |accessdate=19 July 2019 |publisher=USTC News Center |date=27 March 2015}}</ref> From 2015 to 2017, Wan was the president of the [[University of Science and Technology of China]].\n\nWan improved the stability and resolution of [[electrochemical scanning tunneling microscope]] (ECTSM) devices, and resolved a number of related problems, such as the STM imaging mechanisms of various types of chiral molecules. He also designed a series of high-performance electrode materials based on micro/nano composite structures.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Zhang |first1=Qiaoling |title=\u65b0\u5f53\u9009\u9662\u58eb\u4e07\u7acb\u9a8f\uff1a\u51e0\u5341\u5e74\u78e8\u4e00\u5251\u7ec8\u4f1a\u5f00\u82b1\u7ed3\u679c |url=http://scitech.people.com.cn/GB/10525386.html |accessdate=19 July 2019 |agency=\u300a\u79d1\u5b66\u65f6\u62a5\u300b |publisher=people.com.cn |date=7 December 2009}}</ref>\n\nWan was elected as an academician of the Chinese Academy of Sciences in 2009. He is the president of All-China Federation of Returned Overseas Chinese since 2017.<ref>{{cite news |title=\u4e07\u7acb\u9a8f\u5f53\u9009\u4e2d\u56fd\u4fa8\u8054\u4e3b\u5e2d |url=http://www.xinhuanet.com//politics/2017-06/09/c_1121118693.htm |accessdate=19 July 2019 |agency=China News Service |publisher=Xinhuanet}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n*[[HLHL]] Science and Technology Achievement Award (2014)\n*Chemistry Award of [[TWAS]] (2009)\n*2nd-Class Natural Science Award of China (2007)<ref name=\"ICCAS\"/>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Presidents of the University of Science and Technology of China}}\n{{Members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (2009)}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Wan, Lijun}}\n\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alternate members of the 18th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China]]\n[[Category:Chemists from Liaoning]]\n[[Category:Dalian University of Technology alumni]]\n[[Category:Members of the 19th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chinese Academy of Sciences]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Dalian]]\n[[Category:Presidents of the University of Science and Technology of China]]\n[[Category:Tohoku University alumni]]\n[[Category:Educators from Liaoning]]\n[[Category:Communist Party of China politicians from Liaoning]]\n[[Category:People's Republic of China politicians from Liaoning]]\n", "text_old": "{{Chinese name|[[Wan (surname)|Wan]]}}\n'''Wan Lijun''' ({{lang-zh|\u4e07\u7acb\u9a8f}}, born July 1957) is a Chinese chemist, specializing in [[electrochemistry]] and [[surface science]]. He is an academician of the [[Chinese Academy of Sciences]] and a former president of the [[University of Science and Technology of China]].\n\n==Career==\nWan graduated from [[Dalian University of Technology]] in 1982 and received his PhD degree at [[Tohoku University]] in 1996.<ref name=\"ICCAS\">{{cite web |ti